    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Museums containing collections dealing with the development and application of science, scientific ideas, technology, and instrumentation. Like museums of natural science and natural history, science museums have their origins in the Enlightenment. Some of them developed from the collections of learned societies, others from private collections</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>藏品包含科學發展與應用、科學概念、技術，以及使用器械的博物館。科學博物館和自然科學與自然歷史博物館一樣，都源於啟蒙時代。部份藏品來自學術性協會，其他則來自私人藏品。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Musea waarin de ontwikkeling en toepassing van wetenschap, wetenschappelijke ideeën, technologie en instrumenten centraal staat. De eerste wetenschapsmusea (en de eerste natuurhistorische musea) werden geopend in de periode van de verlichting. Vaak begonnen die musea met particuliere collecties of de collecties van wetenschappelijke genootschappen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Museum, das Sammlungen beherbergt, die sich mit der Entwicklung und Anwendung von Naturwissenschaften, naturwissenschaftlichen Vorstellungen, Technologien und Instrumenten befassen. Gleich der naturkundlichen und naturhistorischen Museen, liegen die Ursprünge der technischen Museen in der Zeit der Aufklärung. Einige von ihnen entwickelten sich aus Sammlungen von Gelehrtengesellschaften, andere aus privaten Sammlungen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Museus contendo coleções que tratam do desenvolvimento e aplicação da ciência, ideias científicas, tecnologia e instrumentação. Como os museus de ciências naturais e de história natural, os museus de ciências têm suas origens no Iluminismo. Alguns deles se desenvolveram a partir de coleções de sociedades científicas, outros de coleções particulares </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
